race.comment: NEVERENOUGHLEGO (6) can bounce back. He was found wanting in a plain effort at Kilmore last time when beaten at $1.30 but had been knocking on the door prior with form that would win this. Like him coming back to 1450m and drawn perfectly, he should take a power of catching. COSTA PAROS (4) was unplaced on debut then last start finished third over 1300m at Ararat after being prominent at the corner. Can improve again now and prove hard to hold out. OPEN BAR (7)  is a gelding by Proisir and out of the dam Brookbars on debut for the Busuttin & Young yard. Have to respect off a solid jumpout. PUNIC WAR (8) hasn't been far away in recent efforts and has claims third-up.
